# Edward Woodbridge

Edward Collins Woodbridge (18 September 1794 in Bloomsbury, Middlesex â€“ 11 February 1863 in Paddington, London) was an English amateur cricketer who made 10 known appearances in first-class cricket matches from 1815 until 1819.  He was the elder brother of Frederick Woodbridge.
Career
Edward Woodbridge was mainly associated with Surrey.
